  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The pump operates in prolonged in vivo surgical deployments lasting up to 6 hours continuously, with bearing wear, seal degradation, and motor driver electrical transients documented in post-market surveillance reports as recurrent field events. The CFD model and all validation experiments assume nominal hardware geometry and full electromechanical fidelity throughout; no degraded-hardware or fault-state operating conditions are represented.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
