      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study (2.1 M, 6.4 M, 14.8 M cells) performed at the 5 L/min, 3000 RPM operating point. GCI on NIH = 2.3% between medium and fine grids. Production mesh (6.4 M cells) adopted. Discretization error judged acceptable for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Bench test conditions (fluid temperature, hematocrit, anticoagulant protocol, inlet flow waveform) documented and matched to CFD boundary conditions within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Bench tests conducted in bovine blood at 37 ± 0.5 °C, hematocrit 33 ± 2%, with heparin anticoagulation per ASTM F1841. Inlet flow set by calibrated gear pump; speed controlled by closed-loop tachometer. All five nominal operating points replicated under these conditions. No degraded-fluid or fault-hardware conditions were included in the test matrix, consistent with the nominal-hardware assumption of the CFD model."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "RH < 1 at all five operating points; CFD NIH within 15% of bench-measured NIH at each point.",
      "rationale": "CFD NIH values compared against bench measurements at all five nominal operating points. Maximum relative error 11.4% (at 3 L/min, 3500 RPM). All RH values below 1.0. Output comparison criterion satisfied. Comparisons performed exclusively on nominal-hardware data; no fault-state measurements available for comparison."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "NIH and RH demonstrated to be mechanistically linked to clinical hemolysis outcomes via published literature and regulatory precedent.",
      "rationale": "NIH and RH are FDA-recognized metrics for pump-induced hemolysis per FDA guidance on blood-contacting devices. Published clinical correlations support their use as surrogate endpoints. QOI relevance judged adequate for MRL 2 decision-making under nominal operating assumptions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
