      "rationale": "Formal use-error assessment not required at MRL 2. Simulation setup reviewed by a second analyst; boundary condition inputs cross-checked against test records. No use errors identified during peer review."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis power-law constitutive model selection justified by literature and sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on its documented performance in confined rotating flows. Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model used; sensitivity to model coefficients assessed via ±20% perturbation, yielding NIH variation of ±8%. Model form uncertainty judged acceptable for MRL 2. All model-form assessments conducted under nominal hardware assumptions; fault-induced flow regimes (e.g., bearing-whirl-driven vortex shedding) are not represented in the model form evaluation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs (viscosity, density, hemolysis model coefficients, rotational speed) characterized with uncertainty bounds; sensitivity ranking performed.",
      "rationale": "One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis performed on fluid viscosity (±5%), density (±1%), hemolysis coefficients (±20%), and rotational speed (±2%). Hemolysis model coefficients identified as dominant input. Input uncertainty propagation yields NIH uncertainty band of ±9.5% at 5 L/min, 3000 RPM. Rotational speed perturbation of ±2% represents normal controller tolerance; fault-induced speed excursions (e.g., motor driver electrical short causing momentary overspeed) are not included in the input uncertainty characterization."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
